		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65484716">Well there is Redox which is a Rust based OS. But even in Linux there are efforts to use Rust for certain things in the kernel and also outside. I doubt anyone wants to rewrite for the sake of rewriting but if there is code which is especially vulnerable or important for security then it's a candidate to consider using Rust instead of C.</div>
